        "---\n",
        "title: \"Gen AI vs BERT\"\n",
        "description: \"Comparing Generative AI and BERT models on Amazon retail data — local deployment with Ollama, evaluated on accuracy, recall, and F1 score.\"\n",
        "author: \"Tanishq Katheriya\"\n",
        "date: 2025-12-01\n",
        "image: \"../images/genai.jpg\"\n",
        "categories: [Machine Learning]\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Overview\n",
        "\n",
        "Semester 2 project. Used Amazon retail data to compare a Generative AI model and BERT for a text classification task. Both models were run locally using Ollama and VS Code. Evaluation metrics: accuracy, recall, F1 score. Gen AI outperformed BERT across all three.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Model Performance Comparison"
      ],
      "id": "260c39ec"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: fig-genai\n",
        "#| fig-cap: Gen AI vs BERT — model evaluation metrics\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| code-fold: true\n",
        "\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "metrics = ['Accuracy', 'Recall', 'F1 Score']\n",
        "gen_ai  = [92, 89, 90]\n",
        "bert    = [85, 81, 83]\n",
        "\n",
        "x = np.arange(len(metrics))\n",
        "width = 0.35\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
        "bars1 = ax.bar(x - width/2, gen_ai, width, label='Gen AI',  color='#9b59b6', alpha=0.85)\n",
        "bars2 = ax.bar(x + width/2, bert,   width, label='BERT',    color='#e67e22', alpha=0.85)\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.set_ylim(0, 100)\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Score (%)')\n",
        "ax.set_title('Gen AI vs BERT — Performance on Amazon Retail Data')\n",
        "ax.set_xticks(x)\n",
        "ax.set_xticklabels(metrics)\n",
        "ax.legend()\n",
        "ax.bar_label(bars1, fmt='%d%%', padding=3)\n",
        "ax.bar_label(bars2, fmt='%d%%', padding=3)\n",
        "ax.spines[['top', 'right']].set_visible(False)\n",
        "fig.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "fig-genai",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Radar Chart — Full Profile"
      ],
      "id": "3b6fed85"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: fig-radar\n",
        "#| fig-cap: Radar chart comparing Gen AI and BERT across all metrics\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| code-fold: true\n",
        "\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "labels  = ['Accuracy', 'Recall', 'F1 Score', 'Speed', 'Ease of Use']\n",
        "gen_ai  = [92, 89, 90, 70, 85]\n",
        "bert    = [85, 81, 83, 88, 72]\n",
        "\n",
        "angles = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, len(labels), endpoint=False).tolist()\n",
        "gen_ai_vals = gen_ai + [gen_ai[0]]\n",
        "bert_vals   = bert   + [bert[0]]\n",
        "angles      = angles + [angles[0]]\n",
        "label_vals  = labels + [labels[0]]\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6), subplot_kw=dict(polar=True))\n",
        "ax.plot(angles, gen_ai_vals, 'o-', linewidth=2, label='Gen AI',  color='#9b59b6')\n",
        "ax.fill(angles, gen_ai_vals, alpha=0.2, color='#9b59b6')\n",
        "ax.plot(angles, bert_vals,   'o-', linewidth=2, label='BERT',    color='#e67e22')\n",
        "ax.fill(angles, bert_vals,   alpha=0.2, color='#e67e22')\n",
        "ax.set_thetagrids(np.degrees(angles[:-1]), label_vals[:-1])\n",
        "ax.set_ylim(0, 100)\n",
        "ax.set_title('Model Capability Profile', pad=20)\n",
        "ax.legend(loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.3, 1.1))\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "fig-radar",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
